Whatever value you set through [search api](https://github.com/lorenzofox3/Smart-Table/blob/master/src/stTable.js#L101), it will be given to the filter used. 

```Javascript
    table.search('whatever',{prop:'foo', other:'bar'})
```

will result in
```
var filter = $filter('your filter or angular filter by default')
filter(array, {whatever:{prop:'foo',other:'bar'}})
```

The problem is that angular filter comparator used not to traverse object if an object value was provided (cf angular issue pointed)
```
function comparator(actual, expected){
 //base logic on  expected = {prop:'foo',other:'bar'} and actual is item.birthDate 

}
```

now it is traversed and result in two calls
```
function (actual,expected){
  // expected = 'foo' and actual is item.birthDate.before (undefined)
}
function(actual,expected){
  // expected = 'bar' and actual is item.birthDate.after (undefined)
}
```
which explain why the code breaks when upgrading angular

On smart-table side nothing has changed and it still work as expected: whatever value you pass to search (object, array, string) it will be forwarded to the filter used. However you have to change the logic of your custom filter to be compliant with new angular filter api and I would rather avoid using a comparator

