@LivingProgram the default request disk is 10gb so runs stop once they hit 10gb of data. You can't request more disk as the user disk quota per user is also 10 gb. We have a patch in review that will make all of this logic more transparent. There's also a separate issue that makes uploads bigger than 4gb unreliable which will also be fixed in next release and doesn't require anything on your part. 

@percyliang looks like we retry 720 times. (I think the retry function was written with the expectation that connection failures would happen immediately so 720 times with a 30 second cooldown was thought as a 6 hour retry period). 

The problem is that the worker cannot differentiate between the connection dropping and the server refusing the upload (this is apparently due to how large http requests work in bottle) I'm worried that reducing the number of retries here would reduce the number of retires for all kinds of network troubles.

